This study led by scientists from the National Trust for Scotland will follow bats Pipistrellus pygmaeus and Pipistrellus pipistrellus, as well as bats Myotis daubentoni and Plecottus auritus in the Inverewe gardens in Wester Ross.
Special recording equipment will be placed in key locations around the property to track bat activities during the season.
NHS staff and volunteers will also carry out mobile surveys with manual detectors.
An audio analysis performed by experts on all recordings will determine the frequency of bat calls and what each species is doing.
